checkAssignment

public T checkAssignment(java.lang.Object value)
Returns value. There's no way to actually implement this check in GWT client-side code. In order to prevent users from having to check for the root context in a visitor to avoid a special case, we'll just return the object. If the value really isn't assignable to T, a call to setInModel(Object) will fail in the generated code, which has an explicit cast.

Specified by:
checkAssignment in interface EditorContext<T>
Specified by:
checkAssignment in class AbstractEditorContext<T>
Parameters:

Returns:
